Core:Properties.Core:Property: "LFC channel ('LogFeedChannel').\\n\\nThis is a LOG channel for scripts etc. \\n\\nType +lfc verbose [for a more thorough help]\\nType +lfc service [to list your hooks/ignore list]\\n\\nIt is easy to hook up your own script simply by setting a merry:inherit:lib:log to \. (more info on TWiki)\\n\\nThe LFC channel is like a regular chat channel, except that it stores priority and ID tags in all messages. These tags can then be used to filter the messages you get when you keep LFC enabled, and also the messages you receive when doing a '+lfc recall'."
